    public abstract class AbstractCutGenerator<T extends ModelInterface,W extends MasterData>
extends Object
    This class is used to separate valid inequalities. It can access data from the the master problem through a MasterData object. Each time inequalities have to be separated, the generateInqualities method is invoked. Given the data from the master, the AbstractCutGenerator can then check whether there are any violated inequalities. Typically, one wants to store any inequalities generated for a particular master problem in the corresponding MasterData object such that the master problem has access to the inequalities.
